-- Xing to Add 100 Jobs Next Year, Hamburger Abendblatt Reports
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2011-12-26T15:43:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/xing-to-add-100-jobs-next-year-hamburger-abendblatt-reports.html
Xing AG , a German operator of a
professional networking online community, plans to hire 100
employees next year,  Hamburger Abendblatt  reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Stefan Gross-Selbeck.  Most of the jobs will be added at the Hamburg headquarters,
bringing the number of employees at the site to more than 400,
according to the report. The company also plans to add new
sources of income, such as a pay-to-use search function for
business customers to find new staff, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Gross Sarau, Germany at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
